      "side": 1,
      "message": "The call-site contract is unchanged in practice: this path was already exception-based before this change. On validation failure cloneConversation() returned {} and its only production caller -- the Conversation cloning constructor (conversation.cpp:205, sole instantiation at conversation_module.cpp:812, inside the try block) -- immediately converted the empty result into a throw: conversation.cpp:156 `repository_(std::move(repository ? repository : throw std::logic_error(\"Invalid repository\")))`, caught by the pre-existing catch(const std::exception\u0026) in handlePendingConversation(). This change only refines the exception type on that already-throwing path so the catch site can tell permanent validation failures apart from transient ones.\n\nThe remaining callers on this revision are tests:\n- test/unitTest/conversationRepository/conversationRepository.cpp:1163 exercises a git_clone (network-type) failure, which still returns {} -- unaffected.\n- test/dst/dst.cpp:512 clones valid repositories; before this change a validation failure there would have null-dereferenced on repo-\u003ejoin(), now it throws -- same fatal outcome, better diagnosed.\n\nEncoding the failure mode in the return type cannot work for the production caller: it is a delegating constructor, which has no way to return a status -- the exception is the only channel that crosses it. The throw is documented in the header, including the requirement that new callers must handle it.",
